HTML:
MarkUp Language
Use html tags to create web elements
-h1 - h6 ->header
-p is used for paragraph
-Opening tag: <h1>
-Closing tag:  </h1>
-Example: <h1> How are you? </h1>

CSS: Cascade Style Sheet
Used for adding style such as color, width, height and spacing

There are 3 ways styling/use CSS
-1.Inline: <h1 style="color:red"> How are you? </h1>
-2.Internal: Use style tag inside HTML tag
<style>
h1{
    color:red;
}
<style>
-3.External: Creating an external CSS Sheet.
In styles.css, we can use css files without using <style> keyword
        h1{
            color:red;
        }
Notes: external styling is preferred since it makes the code clean
We should not used tags for styling .Class is the most common way to add styling for HTML 
Class is used for styling multiple elements (. means class)
Id is used for   styling UNIQUE elements. Id should not repeat (# means id)       